= render 'shared/about_modal', id: 'yearlyElectricRatesAboutModal', title: 'About Yearly Electric Rates Data' do
  .d-flex.mb-4
    = render 'shared/modal/about_this_calculation', title: "What is the Blended Rate?" do
      %p.mb-3
        The 
        %strong Blended Rate 
        represents the average cost per kWh across 
        %span.text-primary.fw-bold all consumer sectors 
        (Residential, Commercial, Industrial, etc.). 
      
      %p.mb-3
        This is calculated for 
        %strong each reporting entity 
        by dividing their total annual revenue by their total kWh sold. This provides a high-level view of the overall electric rate, regardless of individual sector rates.

      .bg-light.p-3.border.rounded.small.mb-0
        %ul.list-unstyled.mb-0
          %li
            .text-muted.mb-1 (Total Revenue from All Sectors) ÷ (Total kWh Sold to All Sectors) =
            %strong Result: 
            %span.text-primary.fw-bold Blended Rate per kWh
          
          %li.mt-3.pt-2.border-top
            %span.text-dark.fw-bold Example:
            .mt-1.text-muted
              $1,850,000 Total Revenue ÷ 10,000,000 Total kWh Sold =
            .mt-1
              %strong Result: 
              %span.text-primary.fw-bold $0.185 per kWh
  
  .d-flex.mb-4
    = render 'shared/modal/about_this_calculation', title: "Power Cost Equalization (PCE) Communities" do
      %p.mb-3
        Residential rates in PCE communities are displayed as rates paid by residential customers 
        %strong before and after 
        the PCE subsidy.
        
        %p.mb-3
          The PCE program reduces the cost of electricity in rural Alaska by subsidizing a portion of the rate for residential and qualified community facility use (streetlights, water/sewer utilities, etc.).
    
        .bg-light.p-3.border.rounded.small.mb-0
          %ul.list-unstyled.mb-0
            %li
              %strong.text-dark Residential Cap:
              .text-muted.mt-1
                Subsidies apply to the first 
                %span.text-primary.fw-bold 750 kWh 
                per residential meter per month. Use above this cap is charged at the full unsubsidized rate.
              
            %li.mt-3.pt-2.border-top
              %strong.text-dark Community Facility Cap:
              .text-muted.mt-1
                Total community facility subsidy is limited to 
                %span.text-primary.fw-bold 70 kWh per resident.
              .mt-2
                %span.text-dark.fw-bold Example:
                %div.mt-1
                  100 residents × 70 kWh = 
                  %span.text-primary.fw-bold 7,000 kWh
                  subsidized
    
        %p.mt-3.mb-0.small.text-muted
          %i.bi.bi-info-circle.me-1
          Note: Other non-residential sectors, such as commercial and government (including public schools), are
          %span.fw-bold not covered 
          by PCE subsidies and pay full unsubsidized rates.
